social_posts.post_text:
Time to play some catch up, so enjoy this dump from the past few (several) months 📸
1. New Year's Europe trip with the boys!
2. Meeting with my dear friend, the Former Ambassador from Eswatini to the United States in the field at a @thirstproject build site 💧
3. Uncle Seth moment
4. Celebrating Gill's 1st birthday 🎈🐶
5. Annual friend Wine Trip!
6. Family Time in Indiana for the Holidays 🎄 
7. Can't go wrong with a day at Disney 😎
8. Desert time in Joshua Tree
9. Framily Forever ❤️
10. Rainy days, Warm Hearts in Seattle

We are 🎉 FOUR DAYS 🎉 out from our “Walk for Water” in honor of World Water Day, and our founder, @sethmaxwell1 has a special message for you 💧🙌 It’s not too late to grab those FREE 🎟️, and help end the global water crisis 👀👉 LINK IN BIO, SPREAD THE WORD! #WorldWaterDay #WorldWaterDay2023

Getting old. 😎 One month ago these amazing humans kidnapped me to celebrate officially becoming middle aged. 😳 Getting old isn’t bad at all with you guys by my side. My grandpa always said, “love every age you’re at, because getting old is a gift that not everyone gets.” Onward and upward ❤️

Today is #WorldWaterDay23. Over 700 million people on our planet STILL lack access to safe, clean drinking water. But @thirstproject is a movement of young people working to change this. We WILL be the generation to push the water crisis into the history books. Just $25 gives one person clean water for life! Visit thirstproject.org to learn how to bring @thirstproject to your school, use your voice to raise the profile of the global water crisis, and give. Water is a Human Right. Join the Fight. 
And the work we do simply would not be possible without the support of so many like @myteadrop @sturdrinks & @bellesbeachhouse. Thank you so much.

In case you were confused, let us clear the air!😉

Allow us to FORMALLY introduce ourselves… we are Legacy Youth Leadership!! 🖤 & we are just getting started! 😏😝

We already know I’m the WORST at posting on here, but just got these pics back from @bl_thompson & @ohheyitslindseyshea ‘s wedding back in March and in the feels reliving all the magic. Love you both more than life ❤️
Friend Photo Dump (from the last four months 🙈) …I’m so good at Instagram.

14th Annual #ThirstGala in the books! Easily my favorite night of the year! What a gift to gather our incredible award winners, partners, and supporters in one place to celebrate our work and create more impact together. 💧❤️

THANK YOU SO MUCH for helping make this night magical @paramountpics @unitedtalent @elephante @wishyouwereheregroup @thismessytablela @liquiddeath @thecameronboycefoundation @butter.la @losangelesfloralcouture @advantage_pr  and all of our amazing partners! 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

Massive congratulations to my queen @_moniquecoleman and my brothers from other mothers @mike_manning_ , @nick_tocco, and my dear friend Natalie 🥰

The biggest THANK YOU in the world to our entire @ThirstProject Board, Staff & all of our incredible Volunteers! Extra Special Thanks @wyckgodfrey @tsnowlin & @drmarykerr 🙏🏼❤️

❤️ My Tribe: @chestersee @nicogreetham @dexterdarden @lauramarano @missipyle @michaelwelchact @thevictorboyce @libboyce @maya.elan @kaseyj_728 

My rock: @7mo7 ❤️❤️❤️

The incomparable @ginashainee 💕 

And the King 👑 without whom Gala absolutely would not have happened: @lucasjames24 . I’m so proud of you. 

Big love ❤️💧

social_posts.post_text: Because we Cannes Cannes Cannes!🇫🇷 My body is exhausted but my heart is full. First time being / speaking at @cannes_lions about the work @legacyyouthleadership is doing to support young people in partnership with so many incredible leaders. Biggest thanks ever to @72andsunny_ @pttow and so many more 💛
In true Seth fashion, I'm posting this recap over a month late. Our Team at @legacyyouthleadership hosted our 5th Annual LEGACY SUMMIT this past July, and it was EPIC! Take me back. All the feels 🫶🏼

Can’t believe we’re just a little over one month away from our 3rd Annual #LegacyBall! 

This magical night will raise awareness and support for the incredible students & young people @legacyyouthleadership will serve this upcoming school year. 

Counting down the days ♥️

You know the drill. I post at LEAST a month late and then way too much all at once. I’m SO good at Instagram 🤷‍♂️🤪 August and September have been pretty great. Favorite mems, favorite people ♥️ (including Bey of course)
